{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.4",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 4,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 4",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 4 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.4.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:1",
      "text": "Then Eliphaz the Thæmanite answered and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.4.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:2",
      "text": "Hast thou been often spoken to in distress? but who shall endure the force of thy words?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.4.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:3",
      "text": "For whereas thou hast instructed many, and hast strengthened the hands of the weak one,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.4.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:4",
      "text": "and hast supported the failing with words, and hast imparted courage to feeble knees.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.4.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:5",
      "text": "Yet now that pain has come upon thee, and touched thee, thou art troubled.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.4.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:6",
      "text": "Is not thy fear founded in folly, thy hope also, and the mischief of thy way?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.4.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:7",
      "text": "Remember then who has perished, being pure? or when were the true-hearted utterly destroyed?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.4.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:8",
      "text": "Accordingly as I have seen men ploughing barren places, and they that sow them will reap sorrows for themselves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.4.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:9",
      "text": "They shall perish by the command of the Lord, and shall be utterly consumed by the breath of his wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.4.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:10",
      "text": "The strength of the lion, and the voice of the lioness, and the exulting cry of serpents are quenched.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.4.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:11",
      "text": "The old lion has perished for want of food, and the lions' whelps have forsaken one another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.4.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:12",
      "text": "But if there had been any truth in thy words, none of these evils would have befallen thee. Shall not mine ear receive excellent revelations from him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.4.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:13",
      "text": "But as when terror falls upon men, with dread and a sound in the night,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.4.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:14",
      "text": "horror and trembling seized me, and caused all my bones greatly to shake.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.4.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:15",
      "text": "And a spirit came before my face; and my hair and flesh quivered.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.4.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:16",
      "text": "I arose and perceived it not: I looked, and there was no form before my eyes: but I only heard a breath and a voice, saying,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.4.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:17",
      "text": "What, shall a mortal be pure before the Lord? or a man be blameless in regard to his works?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.4.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:18",
      "text": "Whereas he trusts not in his servants, and perceives perverseness in his angels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.4.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:19",
      "text": "But as for them that dwell in houses of clay, of whom we also are formed of the same clay, he smites them like a moth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.4.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:20",
      "text": "And from morning to evening they no longer exist: they have perished, because they cannot help themselves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.4.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:21",
      "text": "For he blows upon them, and they are withered: they have perished for lack of wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
